ATTACHMENTS:
Photographs of Fuller's injures

NEIGHBORHOOD CHECKS: 
Troopers checked with the surrounding residences and checked the "Wetcher Whistle" liquor store (1220 Old Ocean City Rd, Salisbury) in attempt to locate any further evidence and or witnesses.

NARRATIVE:

On August 19, 2023, at approximately 2128 hours I, Trooper First Class Graves #7199, was dispatched to 113 Benjamin Avenue, Salisbury Wicomico County Maryland 21801 for a possible rape. Upon my arrival to the scene I made contact with the complainants who I would identify as Ina Fuller (2/F DOB:03/28/1966), Joan Johnson (2/F DOB:09/18/1964) and James Pilgrim (2/M DOB:12/08/1963). 

I would observe Fuller to have injuries on her face and scrapes on her right arm and left leg. EMS would respond to the scene and Fuller would later refuse treatment. 

While speaking with Fuller she would state that at approximately 2050 hours she was leaving from a friend's house utilizing her bicycle. Fuller advised she was traveling on Old Ocean City in the area of Civic Avenue near the "Wetcher Whistle" liquor store when a black vehicle (unknown make and model) drove up to her without striking her, but causing her to fall. Fuller continued to state that two black men exited the vehicle and approached her while she was lying on the ground. The men then dragged her back to the black vehicle and would both eventually proceed to penetrate her vaginally with their penises. Fuller was unable to give any detail in regard to a timeline of events that occurred inside the vehicle, she would state it happened quickly and during the incident her shirt had been torn. Fuller would later describe the black men to be approximate age of 20 years, one with a dreadlocks style haircut and the other having a shaved head.  

When attempting to pinpoint the location of where the incident had occurred Fuller would state it was by a sign East of Wetcher Whistle but unknown how far East. Fuller would also state she did not remember passing the Sonoco gas station, but she was traveling on the eastbound lane of Old Ocean City Road. 

When asked if Fuller remembered any further detail to the events that had occurred she would advise she did not and wanted to be left alone. Fuller was asked if she would be willing to consent and complete a Sexual Assault Forensic Evidence kit to which she would continue to state she wanted to be left alone. Johnson and Pilgrim would both state they would attempt to console Fuller and try to also convince her to later proceed with a SAFE Kit. 

When speaking with Johnson and Pilgrim about what had occurred they would advise that she had left earlier in the day and had returned home in this state and 911 was immediately called. 

Troopers conducted neighborhood checks and would speak with neighbors in the surrounding area -
Benjamin Avenue:
111- Female subject identified as Barbra Simmons (2/F DOB: 06/01/1960) would advise that she had been made aware that Fuller had gone missing earlier in the day and the family was actually attempting to locate her. 
112- No answer at the residence
115- No answer at the residence

While competing neighborhood checks a black sedan would arrive to 113 Benjamin avenue. I would make contact with a male and female who identified themselves as family member of Fuller, they would later refuse to give their names. The two individuals would advise that the entire family had been looking for Fuller earlier in the day and believed her to be missing, they would also state that Fuller has known to suffer mental health illnesses and utilizes Suboxone.

Troopers checked the area of "Wetcher Whistle" liquor store in attempt to locate any further evidence and or witness.
"Wetcher Whistle" - 
Cpl. Smith # 6083 would respond to this location and observe no further evidence but would observe the business to have security cameras. It is unknown if the security cameras are operational, the business was closed at the time of this investigation. 

Criminal Enforcement Division was notified of this incident.

Follow Up- 

On August 20, 2023, I would be informed by Sgt. Bowie #5734 via email that Fuller had called the barrack and advised that her medicine had been stolen during the assault and wanted it to be added to the report. 

On August 22, 2023 at approximately 2213 hours I would respond to the area of Old Ocean City Road and Civic Avenue (near the Wetcher Whistle) and conduct a neighborhood check- 
Wetcher Whistle (1220 Old Ocean City Road)-Closed at the time of patrol check, observed cameras but unknown if operational. 
Sunoco (1300 Old Ocean City Road)- Spoke with 1/M cashier who advised he had not seen anything the night of the incident and the business does not have external cameras. 
Bloosurf (1222 Old Ocean City Road)-Closed at the time of patrol check, observed cameras but unknown if operational. 
Shalon Pentecostal Church (1221 Old Ocean City Road)-Closed at the time of patrol check, observed cameras but unknown if operational. 
Wicomico Day School (1315 Old Ocean City Road) - Closed at the time of patrol check, observed cameras but unknown if operational. 

On August 22, 2023, at approximately 2344 hours I would respond to 113 Benjamin Avenue in attempt to make contact with Fuller to ask further questions about the case. Upon my arrival to the scene I would make contact with the female subject identifying as a family member from the night of the incident who refused to give her information and another female subject, identified as Bernadette Pilgrim (2/F DOB:08/27/1967). Pilgrim would advise she is the home owner and friend of Fuller and that Fuller had returned to her residence in Virgina. The female family member would advise that while she drove Fuller back to the Benjamin Avenue address after completing the SAFE kit Fuller would state that she had been on her way home from a party behind "Wetcher Whistle" that night and was struck by a black sedan that would take her back to the location of the party where she was raped and then proceed to drive her back to the location of where she was struck and drop her off at her bike. I would then leave the residence and respond to the barrack in attempt to contact Fuller via phone call. 

On August 23, 2023, at approximately 0030 hours I would contact Fuller via phone call from the Maryland State Police Salisbury Barrack and ask her questions in regards to the case. I would ask Fuller where she had been traveling from on the bike to which she would state from a friends house that was sitting on his porch and a little after 9 pm she advised him she had to return home because it was getting late. Fuller would then change her statement and advise it was actually not a friend but a stranger she had been talking to. I then asked Fuller if she remembered the direction of travel of the vehicle after the incident to which she would advise they continued traveling east on Old Ocean City Road. I would then ask Fuller if she had been struck by the vehicle to which she would advise she was not. I asked Fuller if the suspects made any threats/statements or used any weapons to which she would advise they had not. I would then ask if Fuller fought back against the individuals to which she would advise she did not. 

When I asked Fuller about the medicine she had requested to be added to the report she advised she no longer needed it to be added to the report because her doctor had already approved of the prescription refill. Fuller would inform myself that the prescription medication was Suboxone, but she was unaware of how much. 

Shortly after asking this question Fuller requested the case be closed/dropped, she would also state that she wanted to forget everything and did not want to keep re-living this incident. 

 I request this case be forwarded to CED for further investigation

All events occurred in Wicomico County Maryland.
